choices.text:
what does this command do: ssh -i "~/UserKey.pem" -C -L 25900:localhost:5900 user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com
The command is used to establish a secure connection between two hosts using the SSH protocol. The -i option specifies an identity file (~/.ssh/UserKey.pem) for authentication, and the -C option tells the client to forward all incoming connections. The -L option specifies the local port number (25900) and the remote hostname or IP address (localhost:5900). Finally, the user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com option specifies the username and IP address of the remote server to connect to.
